# .cursorrules — inventory-management
# Cursor reads this file to understand the project context and coding style.

## Tech stack
- Backend: Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2, Maven, JPA/Hibernate, MySQL
- Frontend: React 18, Axios
- Tests: JUnit 5, Mockito, AssertJ, MockMvc
- Containers: Docker, Docker Compose

## Java conventions (Backend)
- Always use constructor injection, never @Autowired on fields
- All public service methods must have complete Javadoc (@param, @return, @throws)
- Use custom exceptions: ResourceNotFoundException and BusinessException
- Use BigDecimal for all monetary values (unitPrice, totalAmount, lineTotal)
- Apply soft delete (active = false), never deleteById()
- Validate all input parameters at the start of each service method
- All entity and method names in English
- Use @Transactional on service methods that modify multiple entities

## Business rules to enforce
- Stock can never go negative — validate before any OUT or ADJUSTMENT movement
- Purchase order status transitions must follow: DRAFT → SUBMITTED → APPROVED → RECEIVED
  CANCELLED is allowed from DRAFT or SUBMITTED only
- SKU must be unique across all products
- Warehouse code must be unique across all warehouses
- Supplier email must be unique across all suppliers
- lineTotal on PurchaseOrderItem must always equal quantity * unitPrice

## Test conventions
- Framework: JUnit 5 + Mockito + AssertJ
- Class annotation: @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
- Method name: methodName_context_expectedResult
- @DisplayName required on every test with a clear English description
- One test per concrete behavior
- Mock only repositories and external dependencies

## React conventions (Frontend)
- Functional components with hooks only, no class components
- JSDoc on each component documenting its props
- Always handle three states: loading (boolean), error (string|null), data
- Format prices with: toLocaleString('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' })
- Format dates with: new Date(dateStr).toLocaleDateString('en-US')
- Show server validation errors field by field, not as a single generic message

## What this project contains for practice
- 18 bugs in backend services (BUG #1–#18)
- 10 bugs in the frontend (BUG #19–#28)
- Incomplete Javadoc marked with TODO throughout
- Missing tests marked with TODO in test files
